Reasoning: The paper discusses the system descriptions of solvers submitted to a competition on computational models of argumentation, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG (machine learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves text analysis and processing, which falls under cs.CL (computational linguistics). Additionally, the paper discusses security and cryptography, which could fall under cs.CR (cryptography and security) and the paper involves algorithms and data structures, which could fall under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms).
